<recipe 
xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io" 
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd"> 
                                                                                
    <title>Three Ingredient Cookies</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    


    <diet>GlutenFree</diet>

    <ingredient>1 cup peanut butter (smooth)</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 cup sugar</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 egg</ingredient>

    <step>
Preheat oven to 180C. In a mixer combine all ingredients and mix until combined.   Scoop out 1 TBSP of mixture and roll into a ball. Place on a line baking sheet. Once sheet is full use the back of a fork to flatten each cookie. Bake in oven for 8-10 minutes.
    </step>
</recipe>